Therometers are devices that are used to measure the temperature of a system. All thermometers are based on the principle that some physical property (known as thermometric property) of a system changes as the system's temperature changes.

**Empirical temperature scale** is a scale of temperature that is based on the variation with temperature of a property of a substance, _assuming_ that the property varies linearly with temperature.

How do we set up an empirical temperature scale?

